PROMPT START

You are turning the following blog into a simple, compelling, ultra-scannable email written specifically for franchisors.
Your goal is to give them the 5 biggest takeaways they need to protect their brand and franchisees—using the fewest words possible.

Audience

Franchisors, multi-brand operators, and founders who want to:

Protect the system

Reduce liability

Strengthen insurance requirements

Support franchisees

Scale with fewer surprises

They are BUSY and skim everything.

RULES (Apply ALL)
Tone & Language (non-negotiable)

5th–6th grade reading level

Simple, human, direct

Zero jargon

Zero corporate speak

Zero filler

Speak to the franchisor, not at them

Focus on their fears, goals, and responsibilities

Email Structure
1. Subject Line

2–6 words

Clear + curiosity-driven

No buzzwords

Must tie to the blog’s biggest insight

Examples:

“A Risk Most Miss”

“Your Brand’s Hidden Gap”

“What Franchisors Forget”

“This Gets Expensive Fast”

2. Short Intro (2 sentences max)

Follow StoryBrand rules:

Sentence 1:
Identify the ONE problem the blog helps franchisors solve.

Sentence 2:
Explain why it matters for protecting the system or franchisees.

3. Top 5 Key Takeaways

Deliver 5 bullets that follow these rules:

Each bullet must:

Be one sentence

Be under 14 words

Use bolded key words

Work as a standalone headline

Focus on simplified, high-level insight

Address franchisor risk, protection, or oversight

Format example:

Hidden liabilities grow fastest when franchisees don’t follow the same coverage rules.

Leave a blank line between bullets.

4. Close with a High-Value CTA

Use this EXACT structure:

If you want the full breakdown so you can protect your brand and franchisees, you can read the full article here: [Insert Link]

Final Output Format

Return the finished email like this:

Subject: [Insert subject line]

Hi there,

[2-sentence intro]

Top 5 takeaways:

[Bullet #1]

[Bullet #2]

[Bullet #3]

[Bullet #4]

[Bullet #5]

If you want the full breakdown so you can protect your brand and franchisees, you can read the full article here: [Insert Link]

Now rewrite the blog below following all rules:
[PASTE BLOG HERE]

PROMPT END
